1
00:01:31,300 --> 00:01:34,010
<i>I'm Katsuki Yuri, a figure 
skater representing Japan</i>

2
00:01:34,010 --> 00:01:36,990
<i>who's in the middle of the Grand 
Prix Series' Cup of China!</i>

3
00:01:36,990 --> 00:01:40,910
<i>I ended the short program in first place 
after scoring a personal high score!</i>

4
00:01:40,910 --> 00:01:43,910
<i>I'm now within reach of my first victory 
in a Grand Prix Series event!</i>

5
00:01:44,260 --> 00:01:45,530
Congratulations, Yuri.

6
00:01:45,530 --> 00:01:46,910
We got really fired up!

7
00:01:46,910 --> 00:01:49,670
That was the hottest performance ever!

8
00:01:49,670 --> 00:01:51,340
Keep it up in your free program!

9
00:01:50,290 --> 00:01:51,340
Yuri, that was awesome!

10
00:01:51,340 --> 00:01:52,420
Good luck!

11
00:01:51,340 --> 00:01:52,420
Awesome, awesome!

12
00:01:52,420 --> 00:01:55,810
China's On! The Grand Prix Series Opening Event!!

13
00:01:52,420 --> 00:01:57,420
Seventh Skate 
China's On! The Grand Prix Series Opening Event!! 
The Cup of China Free Skate

14
00:01:55,810 --> 00:01:57,420
The Cup of China Free Skate.

15
00:02:00,430 --> 00:02:01,750
Yuri, you haven't slept, have you?

16
00:02:01,750 --> 00:02:04,420
I-I-I did! A little bit, anyway.

17
00:02:04,930 --> 00:02:07,310
Nap until this evening's event starts.

18
00:02:07,710 --> 00:02:09,350
It'll be fine.

19
00:02:09,350 --> 00:02:12,690
I always slept in until the last minute
before competitions, too.

20
00:02:13,200 --> 00:02:15,630
Victor! Did you set an alarm?!

21
00:02:18,650 --> 00:02:21,440
We're at the third event of the 
Grand Prix Series, the Cup of China.

22
00:02:21,440 --> 00:02:23,580
The men's singles free skate is about to start!

23
00:02:25,400 --> 00:02:27,330
Huh? It won't open.

24
00:02:28,580 --> 00:02:30,580
Yuri, were you unable to take a nap?

25
00:02:30,580 --> 00:02:31,400
Huh?

26
00:02:31,400 --> 00:02:32,460
I did nap! I did!

27
00:02:32,460 --> 00:02:34,670
I forbid you from doing jumps 
in the six-minute warm-up.

28
00:02:34,670 --> 00:02:35,550
Huh?!

29
00:02:35,550 --> 00:02:37,920
That's an order from your coach, Yuri.

30
00:02:38,570 --> 00:02:40,990
Now, in the second half of the event,

31
00:02:40,990 --> 00:02:42,680
Group 2 is taking the ice.

32
00:02:43,060 --> 00:02:45,200
<i>If he flubs a jump during the warm-up,</i>

33
00:02:45,200 --> 00:02:48,680
<i>he may lose even more confidence, 
and it'd negatively impact his free skate.</i>

34
00:02:48,680 --> 00:02:50,950
<i>Yuri gets nervous easily.</i>

35
00:02:53,440 --> 00:02:55,440
Let's hope skater Katsuki is all right.

36
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:57,940
He looks rather glum after the warm-up.

37
00:02:57,940 --> 00:02:59,690
Oh, my.

38
00:02:58,540 --> 00:02:59,690
That face...

39
00:02:59,690 --> 00:03:02,200
We've seen that face often.

40
00:03:02,860 --> 00:03:06,700
Well, it's common for skaters to nail 
something they flubbed during practice!

41
00:03:08,450 --> 00:03:09,400
I'm sorry...

42
00:03:09,400 --> 00:03:11,440
Well, just continue warming up, nice and easy.

43
00:03:13,530 --> 00:03:15,340
Guang-hong, keep it together.

44
00:03:15,340 --> 00:03:19,090
You have the perfect program that 
we prepared just for today!

45
00:03:18,310 --> 00:03:19,090
Guang-hong!

46
00:03:19,440 --> 00:03:21,610
Become China's hero!

47
00:03:24,810 --> 00:03:28,940
First up is Guang-hong Ji, 
China's young ace, age 17.

48
00:03:28,940 --> 00:03:30,930
He's in sixth place after the short program.

49
00:03:32,020 --> 00:03:35,720
He is skating to "The Inferno," 
from the movie <i>Shanghai Blade</i>.

50
00:03:35,720 --> 00:03:38,460
His theme this year is "bonds and violence."

51
00:03:39,110 --> 00:03:41,920
<i>I went with this music because 
my coach pushed it so hard,</i>

52
00:03:41,920 --> 00:03:45,290
<i>but how does skating as an underworld 
assassin help me become a hero?</i>

53
00:03:47,610 --> 00:03:49,460
Oh! It looks like he over-rotated,

54
00:03:49,460 --> 00:03:52,370
but that's another quadruple toe loop, 
following the one in his short program!

55
00:03:53,580 --> 00:03:56,260
<i>I've been living in Shanghai's seamy underbelly,</i>

56
00:03:56,260 --> 00:03:57,940
<i>but this is my last job.</i>

57
00:03:58,380 --> 00:04:01,050
<i>With my trusty sword, I can 
handle it just fine on my own!</i>

58
00:04:05,170 --> 00:04:08,380
A triple axel, single loop, and a triple Salchow.

59
00:04:09,030 --> 00:04:11,810
<i>All right. It's going even better 
than it did during the warm-up.</i>

60
00:04:12,170 --> 00:04:14,980
He's nailed all his jumps in the first half!

61
00:04:17,860 --> 00:04:21,860
Will he grab a ticket to the Grand Prix Final 
in his very first Grand Prix series?

62
00:04:23,170 --> 00:04:25,280
There will be more jumps in the second half.

63
00:04:26,330 --> 00:04:28,250
A triple flip, followed by a triple toe loop...

64
00:04:28,250 --> 00:04:29,240
He fell!

65
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:33,790
<i>Guess I won't be catching up with a
flawless performance to place first.</i>

66
00:04:34,730 --> 00:04:36,500
A triple loop, followed by a double loop.

67
00:04:36,500 --> 00:04:38,000
He's back on track!

68
00:04:38,000 --> 00:04:39,920
<i>How did the story go from here?</i>

69
00:04:41,260 --> 00:04:43,920
<i>The protagonist infiltrates the enemy 
lair and fights his way to the top,</i>

70
00:04:45,030 --> 00:04:46,570
<i>where the boss awaits.</i>

71
00:04:50,620 --> 00:04:52,310
<i>He is reunited with longtime allies.</i>

72
00:04:52,940 --> 00:04:55,730
<i>Now that the pressure's off, 
there's opportunity!</i>

73
00:04:55,730 --> 00:04:57,790
Here comes the step sequence.

74
00:04:57,790 --> 00:04:59,840
What speed! It's like watching a car chase!

75
00:04:59,840 --> 00:05:01,730
He's taking us right to the climax.

76
00:05:03,460 --> 00:05:06,680
<i>The protagonist has a duel with 
the enemy organization's boss.</i>

77
00:05:06,680 --> 00:05:08,870
<i>His allies are hunted by the organization.</i>

78
00:05:13,730 --> 00:05:15,690
The last jump is a double axel.

79
00:05:16,700 --> 00:05:17,740
Success!

80
00:05:18,570 --> 00:05:21,000
<i>My Grand Prix Series will end here,</i>

81
00:05:21,600 --> 00:05:24,400
<i>but the Four Continents and the 
Worlds are still waiting for me.</i>

82
00:05:25,300 --> 00:05:28,720
<i>I'll raise the technical difficulty of my
programs and claw my way to the podium!</i>

83
00:05:29,650 --> 00:05:34,020
<i>I'm not the kind of man who'd die in a ditch here!</i>

84
00:05:34,020 --> 00:05:38,520
Guang-hong Ji, enveloped in loud applause!

85
00:05:38,520 --> 00:05:39,940
Guang-hong Ji's combined score

86
