well above to place him fifth.

98
00:06:13,850 --> 00:06:17,850
In his free skate, he has prepared 
three quads in the first half.

99
00:06:20,910 --> 00:06:26,690
The first jump is his signature move, 
the high-difficulty quadruple Lutz!

100
00:06:27,890 --> 00:06:28,990
Success!

101
00:06:29,430 --> 00:06:32,540
<i>He's far from where he was at 
the European Championships,</i>

102
00:06:32,540 --> 00:06:35,440
<i>but he's still in competitive 
mode after the short program.</i>

103
00:06:35,440 --> 00:06:36,500
<i>That's unusual.</i>

104
00:06:40,210 --> 00:06:42,000
Next up is a quadruple Salchow.

105
00:06:53,600 --> 00:06:57,530
<i>Next is his triple axel, single loop,
triple Salchow combination.</i>

106
00:06:58,180 --> 00:07:00,140
<i>Take off in front of that ad.</i>

107
00:07:00,500 --> 00:07:01,650
<i>And...</i>

108
00:07:02,000 --> 00:07:02,910
<i>There!</i>

109
00:07:06,170 --> 00:07:08,070
He nailed the jump combination!

110
00:07:09,210 --> 00:07:11,610
Yuri, let's warm up in a different spot.

111
00:07:11,950 --> 00:07:15,240
<i>What's the place with the fewest people?</i>

112
00:07:16,370 --> 00:07:19,910
<i>I'm the only one who can skate 
exactly the way I want.</i>

113
00:07:19,910 --> 00:07:25,030
<i>I thought Victor was the same as me, 
living for life on the ice.</i>

114
00:07:27,450 --> 00:07:29,510
Quadruple Salchow, double toe loop.

115
00:07:29,510 --> 00:07:32,750
That was a perfect landing!

116
00:07:32,750 --> 00:07:38,270
<i>It's not like you to leave the ice and find 
someone you want to protect, Victor.</i>

117
00:07:39,150 --> 00:07:40,270
<i>We met ten years ago,</i>

118
00:07:40,270 --> 00:07:42,270
<i>when you'd won the European Championships</i>

119
00:07:42,720 --> 00:07:44,870
<i>and I'd just debuted in the senior division.</i>

120
00:07:45,800 --> 00:07:47,900
Victor! Congrats!

121
00:07:48,230 --> 00:07:49,460
What's your name?

122
00:07:49,460 --> 00:07:50,900
Christophe Giacometti!

123
00:07:51,840 --> 00:07:53,070
Okay.

124
00:07:54,320 --> 00:07:55,160
Chris,

125
00:07:55,510 --> 00:07:57,160
see you at the Worlds.

126
00:07:57,720 --> 00:07:58,390
Yeah!

127
00:07:59,040 --> 00:08:01,660
<i>Yuri can't surpass you.</i>

128
00:08:01,660 --> 00:08:03,580
<i>I'll win this season!</i>

129
00:08:04,370 --> 00:08:07,790
<i>And I'll bring Victor back to the ice!</i>

130
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,020
A triple axel.

131
00:08:07,020 --> 00:08:09,230
He landed his last jump!

132
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:14,340
<i>The next time you come to stand by me,</i>

133
00:08:14,340 --> 00:08:17,680
<i>I believe I'll be the one 
standing in the middle.</i>

134
00:08:18,540 --> 00:08:20,390
<i>I think I'm gonna come again...</i>

135
00:08:28,980 --> 00:08:30,860
Th-That was perfect!

