147
00:09:14,570 --> 00:09:15,750
A triple axel!

148
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:16,850
<i>Yeah!</i>

149
00:09:16,850 --> 00:09:19,120
<i>I'm going to become Thailand's future!</i>

150
00:09:19,950 --> 00:09:23,730
<i>The audience has been in love with Phichit 
since his short program yesterday.</i>

151
00:09:23,730 --> 00:09:27,500
<i>Unlike Yuri, he has tremendous innate flair.</i>

152
00:09:27,830 --> 00:09:32,990
The loud cheers speak to the high expectations 
we have for Phichit Chulanont.

153
00:09:32,990 --> 00:09:34,840
Coming up next is a triple Lutz.

154
00:09:35,250 --> 00:09:37,130
<i>Chris and Yuri are always ahead of me,</i>

155
00:09:37,130 --> 00:09:41,260
<i>with their two quads and higher 
ratings on their five components.</i>

156
00:09:41,260 --> 00:09:43,720
<i>With only one quad under my belt,</i>

157
00:09:44,090 --> 00:09:48,100
<i>the only way I can stay ahead is to put all my 
quads in the second half for more points!</i>

158
00:09:48,100 --> 00:09:51,060
<i>I'm the one who'll advance 
to the Grand Prix Final!</i>

159
00:09:51,560 --> 00:09:55,650
This expressive footwork is also one of 
his unique qualities as a Thai skater.

160
00:09:55,980 --> 00:09:59,140
Here come the jumps in the 
second half, the first quad...

161
00:09:59,140 --> 00:10:00,230
A quadruple toe loop!

162
00:10:00,230 --> 00:10:01,910
Success!

163
00:10:03,130 --> 00:10:06,580
<i>Until very recently, I bet no 
one thought a Thai skater</i>

164
00:10:06,830 --> 00:10:10,080
<i>would land a quad at a Grand Prix series event.</i>

165
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:12,310
<i>I've always believed in myself, though!</i>

166
00:10:15,330 --> 00:10:17,560
Quadruple toe loop, followed by 
a double toe loop!

167
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:19,550
He landed the second quad, too!

168
00:10:17,560 --> 00:10:19,550
Bravo!

169
00:10:29,230 --> 00:10:32,350
<i>It's something only I can do,
not copying anyone else.</i>

170
00:10:32,350 --> 00:10:37,150
The only remaining jumps are a triple flip, 
single loop, double flip combination.

171
00:10:41,950 --> 00:10:43,160
He nailed it!

172
00:10:43,160 --> 00:10:45,370
All his jumps were flawless!

173
00:10:45,850 --> 00:10:47,370
Figure skating history in Thailand...

174
00:10:47,370 --> 00:10:48,680
no, in Asia...

175
00:10:48,680 --> 00:10:52,210
is being rewritten before our eyes

176
00:10:52,890 --> 00:10:55,210
by 20-year-old Phichit Chulanont!

177
00:10:58,480 --> 00:10:59,170
Okay.

178
00:11:07,850 --> 00:11:08,730
Don't listen!

179
00:11:14,520 --> 00:11:17,670
In his first event, Skate America, 
Chulanont finished fourth.

180
00:11:17,670 --> 00:11:20,610
In his second event, the Cup of China, 
will he score his first victory?

181
00:11:20,610 --> 00:11:23,720
If so, he'll be on the cusp of 
becoming the first Thai skater

182
00:11:23,720 --> 00:11:26,150
to advance to the Grand Prix Final!

183
00:11:26,150 --> 00:11:30,150
Oh! His total score is 285.76!

184
00:11:30,150 --> 00:11:31,790
He took the lead over Giacometti!

185
00:11:30,730 --> 00:11:31,500
Yeah!

186
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:33,050
Well done, student.

187
00:11:31,790 --> 00:11:33,800
This is his season's top score, of course!

188
00:11:33,800 --> 00:11:36,190
Please root for me in the Grand Prix Final!

189
00:11:36,190 --> 00:11:38,230
Hey, you don't know if you'll make it yet.

190
00:11:38,230 --> 00:11:39,510
Oh, right.

191
00:11:39,510 --> 00:11:41,920
I won Skate America.

192
00:11:41,920 --> 00:11:42,560
That's right!

193
00:11:42,560 --> 00:11:44,250
I ended yesterday's short program in third.

194
00:11:44,250 --> 00:11:44,870
Well done!

195
00:11:44,870 --> 00:11:48,330
Of everyone here, I'm the 
closest to the Grand Prix Final!

196
00:11:48,330 --> 00:11:49,140
That's right!

197
00:11:51,280 --> 00:11:53,980
Representing the United States, 
Leo de la Iglesia, age 19.

198
00:11:57,360 --> 00:12:00,880
<i>I understand how you might be 
affected by other skaters' standings</i>

199
00:12:00,880 --> 00:12:02,030
<i>if you were younger.</i>

200
00:12:02,030 --> 00:12:04,360
<i>But why is Yuri so nervous?</i>

201
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:07,870
<i>How can I motivate Yuri?</i>

202
00:12:08,760 --> 00:12:09,950
<i>I have no idea.</i>

203
00:12:09,950 --> 00:12:11,780
V-Victor?

204
00:12:11,780 --> 00:12:13,610
It's almost time.

205
00:12:13,610 --> 00:12:14,730
We need to get back.

206
00:12:18,410 --> 00:12:21,920
<i>Skaters' hearts are as fragile as glass.</i>

207
00:12:24,930 --> 00:12:26,590
<i>If their hearts are so fragile...</i>

208
00:12:27,560 --> 00:12:28,330
Yuri.

209
00:12:28,750 --> 00:12:29,430
Huh?

210
00:12:29,430 --> 00:12:33,690
<i>Let's try shattering his into pieces.</i>

211
00:12:34,590 --> 00:12:38,980
If you mess up this free skate 
and miss the podium,

212
00:12:40,200 --> 00:12:42,440
I'll take responsibility by 
resigning as your coach.

213
00:12:55,310 --> 00:12:59,460
Why would you say something like that, 
like you're trying to test me?

214
00:12:59,460 --> 00:13:01,210
<i>It shattered!</i>

215
00:13:01,210 --> 00:13:02,920
Uh, sorry, Yuri.

