242
00:14:11,450 --> 00:14:12,950
He said he hopes people will notice

243
00:14:12,950 --> 00:14:15,540
his new range of artistic 
expression in his performance.

244
00:14:15,850 --> 00:14:19,930
<i>Sorry I cast an eternal curse 
on you, my princess.</i>

245
00:14:20,670 --> 00:14:23,210
<i>I'm sure you've been waiting for 
your prince's kiss all this time.</i>

246
00:14:28,220 --> 00:14:29,830
Here comes a triple loop.

247
00:14:36,620 --> 00:14:37,670
Let's go.

248
00:14:37,670 --> 00:14:38,690
Anya?

249
00:14:39,640 --> 00:14:41,630
<i>Anya, don't run away!</i>

250
00:14:41,630 --> 00:14:43,530
<i>I'm the one who'll protect you!</i>

251
00:14:44,880 --> 00:14:46,110
<i>No!</i>

252
00:14:46,110 --> 00:14:48,850
<i>Anya, it can't be true!</i>

253
00:14:49,680 --> 00:14:50,990
<i>I refuse to believe it!</i>

254
00:14:54,660 --> 00:14:56,600
Next up is a quadruple Salchow.

255
00:14:59,160 --> 00:15:00,210
He fell!

256
00:15:00,210 --> 00:15:01,670
<i>Wake up!</i>

257
00:15:01,670 --> 00:15:04,540
<i>Of all my students, you've been the
most receptive to my instructions.</i>

258
00:15:04,540 --> 00:15:06,300
<i>That was one of your weaknesses, as well.</i>

259
00:15:07,030 --> 00:15:10,410
<i>But this program realizes all the 
things Victor lacks as a skater.</i>

260
00:15:10,410 --> 00:15:12,260
<i>Skate with more confidence!</i>

261
00:15:22,820 --> 00:15:24,400
Next is a triple flip.

262
00:15:25,770 --> 00:15:26,640
Great!

263
00:15:26,640 --> 00:15:29,110
He carries himself with such dignity!

264
00:15:30,480 --> 00:15:32,110
<i>"Please wake me up."</i>

265
00:15:32,660 --> 00:15:34,820
<i>I can hear your voice, Anya.</i>

266
00:15:34,820 --> 00:15:37,870
<i>No matter what happens, I will kiss you.</i>

267
00:15:38,210 --> 00:15:39,870
<i>I promise to save you.</i>

268
00:15:39,870 --> 00:15:41,840
<i>I'll always be your ally.</i>

269
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:43,880
<i>That's why I promise to save you.</i>

270
00:15:45,210 --> 00:15:47,320
<i>I'll save you right now.</i>

271
00:15:47,320 --> 00:15:48,510
<i>You're not alone.</i>

272
00:15:52,880 --> 00:15:56,550
<i>Victor, how does it feel to watch me 
from where you're standing now?</i>

273
00:15:56,960 --> 00:15:59,350
<i>From now on, it's my time to shine!</i>

274
00:15:59,350 --> 00:16:02,850
Oops, I forgot to watch the free skate.

275
00:16:03,230 --> 00:16:05,090
I wonder if Yuri-kun's okay.

276
00:16:05,530 --> 00:16:06,900
Don't his eyes look red?

277
00:16:07,260 --> 00:16:08,630
You're right!

278
00:16:08,630 --> 00:16:10,820
I wonder if something happened 
between him and Victor.

279
00:16:11,790 --> 00:16:13,410
<i>"You don't have to say anything."</i>

280
00:16:13,410 --> 00:16:16,160
Just have more faith than I do that I'll win!

281
00:16:16,600 --> 00:16:20,660
<i>I should have asked Yakov what to do
as a coach in situations like this.</i>

282
00:16:20,660 --> 00:16:24,330
Georgi Popovich's total score is 252.44.

283
00:16:20,660 --> 00:16:32,670
RK: 3 
Georgi Popovich     Total

284
00:16:24,330 --> 00:16:25,770
He's currently in third place.

285
00:16:25,770 --> 00:16:27,500
I must take this program

286
00:16:27,500 --> 00:16:30,670
to the next level before the Russian Nationals.

287
00:16:30,670 --> 00:16:32,660
There's a lot to work on.

288
00:16:48,470 --> 00:16:50,800
We now have our last skater on the ice,

289
00:16:50,800 --> 00:16:53,260
Katsuki Yuri from Japan, in first 
place after the short program.

290
00:16:53,260 --> 00:16:56,030
<i>If your student's trying to console you,</i>

291
00:16:56,030 --> 00:16:58,990
<i>you still have a long way 
to go as a coach, Vitya.</i>

292
00:16:58,990 --> 00:17:01,400
He is skating to "Yuri on Ice."

293
00:17:03,280 --> 00:17:05,370
<i>I feel a lot better after crying.</i>

294
00:17:06,140 --> 00:17:10,960
<i>Victor's expression when I started 
to cry was priceless.</i>

295
00:17:10,960 --> 00:17:12,710
<i>Why is he smiling?</i>

296
00:17:13,820 --> 00:17:16,500
<i>I've cried after a match before,</i>

297
00:17:16,500 --> 00:17:18,440
<i>but that's the first time before a match.</i>

298
00:17:18,710 --> 00:17:20,390
<i>Um, so the first jump...</i>

299
00:17:20,390 --> 00:17:23,730
<i>A quadruple toe loop, 
double toe loop combination.</i>

300
00:17:24,860 --> 00:17:26,600
Quadruple... Double.

301
00:17:30,970 --> 00:17:31,980
<i>Better than I expected.</i>

302
00:17:32,980 --> 00:17:35,240
His first quad was a success.

303
00:17:36,010 --> 00:17:41,490
In this free skate, Katsuki Yuri plans to do 
three quads of two different types.

304
00:17:41,850 --> 00:17:44,660
He's unusually relaxed today.

305
00:17:52,250 --> 00:17:55,390
<i>Victor's too inexperienced as a coach.</i>

306
00:17:55,390 --> 00:17:59,220
<i>It's not like my mental weakness 
started just now.</i>

307
00:17:59,640 --> 00:18:01,510
<i>He should be prepared for this much.</i>

308
00:18:02,430 --> 00:18:03,140
<i>Stupid Victor!</i>

309
00:18:03,850 --> 00:18:05,270
A quadruple Salchow.

310
00:18:05,270 --> 00:18:06,430
<i>Oh, I made it.</i>

311
00:18:06,430 --> 00:18:08,190
Perfect, Yuri!

312
00:18:10,670 --> 00:18:12,900
His theme for this season is "love."

313
00:18:13,170 --> 00:18:14,320
Love 
Katsuki Yuri

314
00:18:14,970 --> 00:18:16,650
Now that I know what love 
is and am stronger for it,

315
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:19,660
I'll prove it to myself with a 
Grand Prix Final gold medal!

316
00:18:19,660 --> 00:18:22,910
Katsuki Yuri made an emphatic 
declaration at the press conference.

317
00:18:27,020 --> 00:18:28,020
A triple loop.

318
00:18:28,020 --> 00:18:29,410
Beautiful.

319
00:18:51,440 --> 00:18:53,370
Next is one of his favorites, the triple axel.

320
00:18:54,650 --> 00:18:56,480
Oops, he touched down!

321
00:18:57,790 --> 00:19:00,460
<i>I might have messed up on 
controlling the jump's speed.</i>

322
00:19:00,460 --> 00:19:02,770
<i>It went pretty well, despite not 
doing it during warm-up.</i>

323
00:19:02,770 --> 00:19:04,350
<i>Next up is a triple flip.</i>

324
00:19:05,090 --> 00:19:07,770
<i>Oh, I wonder how Victor would react</i>

325
00:19:07,770 --> 00:19:11,760
<i>if I made the last quad a 
flip instead of a toe loop.</i>

326
00:19:12,300 --> 00:19:16,420
Coming next is a triple axel, single 
loop, triple Salchow combination.

327
00:19:20,340 --> 00:19:21,970
He over-rotated that one.

328
00:19:24,410 --> 00:19:27,600
<i>I over-rotated, but I'm not as tired 
as I should be, given I haven't slept.</i>

329
00:19:27,600 --> 00:19:30,230
A triple Lutz, triple toe loop combination.

330
00:19:30,230 --> 00:19:32,650
Even in the second half, he's not 
showing any sign of fatigue.

331
00:19:32,650 --> 00:19:35,610
Moving on to the step sequence.

332
00:19:36,180 --> 00:19:37,400
<i>I want to become stronger...</i>

333
00:19:38,480 --> 00:19:39,860
<i>I can become stronger.</i>

334
00:19:40,560 --> 00:19:44,130
<i>I can surpass Victor's wildest imagination!</i>

335
00:19:58,230 --> 00:20:01,170
He's planned a quadruple toe 
loop for his final jump.

336
00:20:04,430 --> 00:20:07,400
I-It's a quadruple flip!

337
00:20:07,400 --> 00:20:10,860
He fell, but there appeared 
to be enough rotations!

338
00:20:10,860 --> 00:20:14,510
The quadruple flip was a signature move 
of Victor Nikiforov, his coach.

339
00:20:14,510 --> 00:20:16,750
Not even Nikiforov ever 
did a jump this difficult

340
00:20:16,750 --> 00:20:20,830
at the end of a program, 
when fatigue would be at its peak!

341
00:20:20,830 --> 00:20:24,300
Here's a man who'll go above and 
beyond our expectations,

342
00:20:24,300 --> 00:20:25,910
Katsuki Yuri!

343
00:20:26,700 --> 00:20:28,360
Huh? Huh?

344
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:29,200
Was that a flip?

345
00:20:32,260 --> 00:20:33,130
<i>Is he crying?</i>

346
00:20:33,570 --> 00:20:34,590
<i>Is he mad?</i>

347
00:20:35,210 --> 00:20:36,710
<i>Which is it?</i>

348
00:20:42,470 --> 00:20:43,410
Victor!

349
00:20:43,970 --> 00:20:45,970
I did great, right?

350
00:21:01,930 --> 00:21:04,390
This was the only thing I could think of

351
00:21:04,390 --> 00:21:06,340
to surprise you more 
than you've surprised me.

352
00:21:07,350 --> 00:21:08,330
Really?

353
00:21:09,960 --> 00:21:12,780
<i>In the Cup of China, 
Phichit-kun won his first gold,</i>

354
00:21:13,320 --> 00:21:15,960
<i>and I kept Chris in check to win silver.</i>

355
00:21:16,620 --> 00:21:19,710
Now that Yuri can do a quadruple flip,

356
00:21:19,710 --> 00:21:22,460
he'll definitely win at the Rostelecom Cup

357
00:21:22,460 --> 00:21:24,880
and advance to the Grand Prix Final.

358
00:21:24,880 --> 00:21:27,650
I'm looking forward to going 
to Russia as his coach.

359
00:21:27,650 --> 00:21:28,890
Did you hear that?

360
00:21:31,150 --> 00:21:34,140
I'll make you into borscht in Moscow,

361
00:21:34,650 --> 00:21:36,890
you pig bastard!

362
00:21:36,890 --> 00:21:39,940
To Be Continued!!!

363
00:23:10,330 --> 00:23:13,200
Say the name of the Moscow airport 
we're heading to ten times, Yuri.

364
00:23:13,200 --> 00:23:15,790
Sheremetyevo, Sheremetyevo, 
Sheremetyevo, Sheremetyevo, Shere...

365
00:23:15,790 --> 00:23:17,950
Next time, Eighth Skate: Yuri vs. Yuri.

366
00:23:17,950 --> 00:23:20,290
The Horror!! Rostelecom Cup, Short Program.

367
00:23:19,790 --> 00:23:24,840
Eighth Skate 
Yuri vs. Yuri 
The Horror!! Rostelecom Cup, Short Program

368
00:23:20,290 --> 00:23:21,790
One step from the Grand Prix Final!

369
00:23:21,790 --> 00:23:23,620
From Russia with love.

